<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 50,000 EXPECTED AT ANNUAL FIESTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For one day, the city's population will almost double as downtown streets 
swell with visitors celebrating the seventh annual San Clemente Fiesta Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 50,000 people are expected to pack two downtown blocks on Avenida 
del Mar to enjoy special events such as a 5K run and the annual Salsa 
Challenge. 
</P>
<P>
 For those with competitive spirits and big appetites, separate contests will 
be held to determine who can eat the most pickles, pies and watermelon. Other 
competitions will be held to discover who is the best at Hula-Hoop and tortilla 
tossing. 
</P>
<P>
 Called the Fiesta 5000 Run/Stride/Walk, the 5K run will start at 8 a.m., 
although day-of-event sign-up will begin two hours earlier. Leisurely 
competitors and serious runners alike will run through the scenic hills and 
streets of San Clemente. Most contestants are expected to be finished by 10 
a.m., and an awards ceremony will take place at that time at Avenida del Mar 
and El Camino Real. 
</P>
<P>
 The street fair will be 9 a.m. to 7 p.m., with live bands and shows.  
</P>
<P>
 Past featured performers have included Rita Coolidge and the Coasters. This 
year's main act will be the Fabulous Jetsons Rocket-Roll show. 
</P>
<P>
 Food and game booths will line Avenida del Mar, many of them staffed by 
community groups that use the proceeds for charity work. 
</P>
<P>
 For salsa lovers, tasting for the competition will start at 11 a.m. Visitors 
can take a free shuttle that will leave from San Clemente High School.  
</P>
<P>
 Several streets will be closed starting at 6 a.m., including El Camino Real 
from Avenida Valencia to El Portal; West Portal and side streets bordering Max 
Berg Plaza Park. Avenida del Mar will be closed between El Camino Real and 
Calle Seville.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
