<P>
 A 16-year-old boy was wounded Thursday night in a gang-related shooting, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy, not identified because of his age, was listed in critical condition 
Friday at an undisclosed hospital, Orange police Sgt. Barry Weinstein said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, described by police as an Anaheim gang member, was in a car 
stopped at Katella Avenue and Glassell Street at 9:30 p.m. when two youths 
thought to be rivals pulled alongside in a pickup truck. The truck's driver 
asked the four occupants of the car where they were from and then fired a 
handgun, Weinstein said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, riding in the back seat, was hit in the upper body. 
</P>
