</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to make the dropping off of children at Moulton Elementary School 
easier for parents, the City Council this week approved eliminating parking on 
the east side of Highlands Avenue just north of the school entrance. 
</P>
<P>
 A loading zone will be created along Highlands for 150 feet north of the 
entrance.Members of the Police Auxiliary Citizens Team, who help with traffic 
control at schools, had suggested the change and said parents had to zigzag 
around parked cars to find enough curb space to drop off children. 
</P>
<P>
 Along with the creation of the loading zone, "No U-turn" signs will be posted 
on Highlands in front of the school. Although U-turns there are legal, city 
staff said the U-turns caused congestion and posed a safety hazard. LYNN FRANEY 
