<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: PROBABLY MAKING A RUN FOR THE BORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Newsday 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Taco Bell customers at the store in Shirley, N.Y., didn't get the order 
they paid $3 for at the drive-up window on May 1, but they didn't complain. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead of the seven-layer chicken burrito and two Meximelts inside their bag, 
they found the day's receipts for the store -- $1,940 in cash.Now the police 
want them for grand larceny. 
</P>
<P>
 Explained Detective Lt. Dennis Caine: "The night manager was putting together 
the receipts for a night deposit. She went over to the counter, pulled a bag 
and put the bank bag inside. The girl working the window grabbed the bag, 
thinking it was an order, and handed it to the people outside. 
</P>
<P>
 "Who looks in a Taco Bell bag?" 
</P>
<P>
 The man and woman have not been seen since. 
</P>
</TEXT>
