<P>
BOWL ATTENDANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Contrary to the suggestion of Daniel Cariaga in his review ("Bamert Inspires 
Quality Performance," July 23), attendance is not down at the Hollywood Bowl 
this summer. Despite the oft-rehashed woes of our area, business at the Bowl is 
actually up 5% over last year.Subscriptions have held steady -- an improved 
trend contradicting industrywide experiences -- and single-ticket sales are 
increasing significantly for all events. In fact, we are projecting a record 
summer at the Bowl with our second year of million-plus attendance.  
</P>
<P>
 This clearly reflects both a great desire for music and a recognition that it 
can be found -- affordably and in the widest possible variety -- at the 
Hollywood Bowl. The Philharmonic is delighted with this achievement. We are 
proud of our artists and staff and happy that more people than ever are turning 
to L.A.'s music oasis for their summer art and entertainment. 
