<HEADLINE>
<P>
'PICKET FENCES' DESERVES A WRITING NOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 From its Emmy nominations, the Academy of Television Arts & Sciences sent a 
message that there was not one drama series deserving recognition in the 
writing category other than "NYPD Blue" ("Emmys Take On a 'Blue' Shade," July 
22). That does not bode well for the future of commercial television. 
</P>
<P>
 Congratulations to the producers, writers, cast and crew of "NYPD Blue" on 
their record 26 Emmy nominations. However, in writing, there is a far more 
deserving drama series that was sorely overlooked: "Picket Fences." 
</P>
<P>
 Arguably one of the most topical and thought-provoking dramatic series in 
television history, each episode of "Picket Fences" challenges viewers by 
presenting real-life ethical dilemmas and issues while also provoking smiles, 
tears and laughs. 
</P>
<P>
 RICK SCOTT 
