<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A police crackdown, billed as one of the largest anti-prostitution operations 
in city history, targeted 33 Manhattan brothels and produced 111 arrests. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said police began the sweep by checking out ads for "hostesses." 
Undercover officers then posed as clients Wednesday night. 
</P>
