<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSINESS PACS SPENT 3 TIMES MORE THAN LABOR ON CONGRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business political action committees donated $203 million to current members 
of Congress during the six years ending in 1993, more than three times as much 
as PACs linked to labor unions, the political watchdog group Common Cause 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Business outspent labor in donations to Democrats in the House of 
Representatives, $72.7 million to $57.5 million. The difference was even more 
lopsided in donations to Republicans, with businesses donating $58.8 million, 
compared to labor's $4.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Senate, businesses outspent labor 2 to 1 on the Democratic side, $32.2 
million to $15.2 million. Business donated $39.8 million to Republicans, 
compared to only $1.5 million by labor groups. 
</P>
