<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; CHAMBER CLASS BUILDS LEADERSHIP SKILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Greater Ventura Chamber of Commerce wants to help train future community 
leaders by sponsoring a special class designed to help those interested in 
public service to improve their communication and problem-solving skills. 
</P>
<P>
 The chamber will hold a breakfast on Thursday to preview the monthly class, 
entitled "Touch of Leadership Ventura." 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Barroca, executive vice president of the chamber, said similar classes 
have been run by chambers in other cities throughout the country and have 
proven successful. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the Ventura class will offer 10 sessions for a charge of $700. The 
class starts Sept. 13 and ends June 10, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is aimed at trying to develop upcoming community leaders," Barroca said. 
"We want to give them a knowledge of all aspects of the city and county -- the 
education system, the political system, the government system." 
</P>
<P>
 The preview breakfast will provide a chance to find out more by talking with 
graduates of the program from other cities. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8 a.m. event costs $5 per person and will be held at the Wedgewood Banquet 
Center on Olivas Park Drive in Ventura. For a class application, call the 
chamber at 648-2875. JASON GRANT 
</P>
</TEXT>
