<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ANGELS/DEMONS -- Are angels and demons real beings? That question will be 
posed to Mormon, Unitarian, Buddhist and Roman Catholic panelists Thursday 
night in a discussion involving audience participation at Northridge 
Seventh-day Adventist Church. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is part of a series sponsored by the San Fernando Valley 
Interfaith Council to explore in open forums the views of different faiths on 
religious and moral topics. The moderator for the panels is the Rev. Jeff 
Utter, pastor of the Congregational Church of Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
 The panelists will be Keith Atkinson, state public affairs director for the 
Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints; Deryck True, president of the 
Studio City Unitarian Universalist Society; Paula Jakunin Fuld, an ordained lay 
Zen Buddhist practitioner, and Jesuit Father Andrew Diviney of Our Lady of 
Lourdes Parish Center, Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 After the panelists speak for five minutes each and exchange remarks to one 
another, the audience will be invited to ask questions. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event will begin at 7:30 p.m. The church is at 17700 Plummer St. For 
information, call event chairman Sam Alster at (818) 343-1205. 
</P>
<P>
 DISABILITIES -- Wheelchair-bound Joni Eareckson-Tada, a widely admired 
painter, writer and speaker in evangelical circles, will be a special guest 
during an afternoon picnic for people with disabilities at Paramount Ranch in 
the Santa Monica Mountains. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which includes games and entertainment, is being sponsored by the 
Church in the Canyon, 4235 Las Virgenes Road, Calabasas. That congregation will 
also observe Disability Awareness Sunday during its 9:30 a.m. service. 
</P>
<P>
 The outdoor program will begin at 3 p.m. and end at 7 p.m. For information, 
call (805) 376-2517. 
</P>
<P>
 HASIDIC STORIES -- In a tribute to the late Rebbe Menachem Schneerson and his 
predecessors in the Hasidic movement in Judaism, author-speaker Sol Marshall 
will tell Hasidic stories and parables during a 10:15 a.m. program Friday at 
the Valley Storefront Multiservice Center for Seniors, 12821 Victory Blvd., 
North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is free. 
</P>
<P>
 MARRIAGE ENHANCEMENT -- An information seminar on the Jewish Marriage 
Enhancement program will be presented at 7:30 p.m. Tuesday at Burbank Temple 
Emanu El, 1302 N. Glenoaks Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Like similar programs in Christian churches, Jewish Marriage Enhancement is 
designed for couples who have been married at least two years and have a 
fundamentally good marriage, to bring their relationship to its fullest 
potential. 
</P>
<P>
 For information on the free seminar, call the temple at (818) 845-1734. 
</P>
<P>
 News and announcements for this column may be sent to Religion Desk, Los 
Angeles Times, 20000 Prairie St., Chatsworth 91311. JOHN DART 
</P>
</TEXT>
