<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; RICKEY HENDERSON DENIES 
ALLEGATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Outfielder Rickey Henderson of the Oakland Athletics denies claims by his 
half-sister that he repeatedly raped her as a youth.In a lawsuit filed Thursday 
in Alameda County Superior Court, Paula Henderson, 31, alleges that the sexual 
assaults started when she was 8 and continued into her teens. The suit alleges 
that suppressed her memories of abuse until about a year ago when she gave 
birth to her first child. Rickey Henderson, 35, issued a statement Friday 
calling the allegations "totally untrue." 
</P>
