<P>
BLADES CLINCH DIVISION TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Blades clinched the Roller Hockey International Pacific 
Division title by defeating the San Jose Rhinos, 9-4, in front of 7,099 at the 
Forum on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Leading, 2-1, at halftime, the Blades took control of the game with 
back-to-back goals by Nick Vachon and Steve Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory improves the Blades to 16-4 and 32 points, five ahead of the 
second place Anaheim Bullfrogs with two games remaining. 
</P>
