<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; BOB NAVARRO OPENS HIS 'JOURNAL' SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Veteran Los Angeles journalist Bob Navarro begins a weekly public-affairs 
series Sunday on KCBS-TV Channel 2, where he is director of editorials and 
station affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 The first installment of "Bob Navarro's Journal," at 4:30 p.m. examines the 
"Save Our State" initiative, which asks for the denial of public school and 
MediCal-related services to undocumented residents and their children. 
Scheduled to appear are Ron Prince, an Orange County accountant and co-author 
of the initiative; Ed Vincent, mayor of Inglewood, and Los Angeles County 
Sheriff Sherman Block. 
</P>
<P>
 Future shows will discuss the resurgence of tuberculosis in Southern 
California, the use of celebrity spokespersons to sell community causes and the 
escalating numbers of hit-and-run accidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
