<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH BASEBALL ROUNDUP; THOUSAND OAKS GAINS WESTERN REGIONAL BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Standout defensive plays in the seventh inning gave the Thousand Oaks Little 
League 13-year-old all-star team a 7-5 victory over South Mission Viejo and the 
Southern California Division II championship in La Mirada. 
</P>
<P>
 With two runners on base and one out in the seventh, first baseman Jon Shepard 
made an over-the shoulder catch down the right-field line, then third baseman 
Ryan Ayers backhanded a line drive to end the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Right-handers Matt Rogers and Chris Strauser combined for Thousand Oaks, and 
Strauser was the winning pitcher for the third consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks opens the four-team Western Regional tournament in San Jose on 
Sunday against the champion from a division encompassing the Pacific Northwest 
and Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 The Western Regional winner advances to the World Series in Taylor, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Senators 21, Dublin, Ohio 1 -- Jared Krehbiel led the Westlake 
Senators in the first round of the Continental Amateur Baseball Assn. 
14-year-old World Series in Dublin. 
</P>
<P>
 Krehbiel drove in four runs with a home run and a triple. The game was called 
after five innings. Westlake banged out 15 hits and Chris Parker and Jeremy 
Sugarman each drove in four runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake plays a doubleheader today. The Senators take on Enid, Okla., then 
face a team from Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
 Indiana 6, Westoaks Senators 5 -- Westoaks concluded play in the Amateur 
Athletic Union Junior Olympics 16-year-old tournament and finished with a 3-4 
record. 
</P>
<P>
 Westoaks trailed, 6-3, in the bottom of the seventh and pulled to within one 
run on a single by Steve Udell that scored Jason Simmons and Matt Riordan. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Holmes batted .500, Ryan Lane hit .435 and Brent Hirsh hit .381 in the 
tournament. 
</P>
