<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOT A MINDLESS SNUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The fact that "Roseanne" was once again snubbed for a best comedy series Emmy 
nomination is good news to those of us who prefer our television comedyon the 
intelligent side ("TV Academy Is Snubbing 'Roseanne,' " July 23). 
</P>
<P>
 The success of such excellent, intelligent shows as "Frasier," "Northern 
Exposure," "Seinfeld" and "Murphy Brown" seems to indicate that once again the 
networks are aiming for our minds instead of the gutter. Keep up the good work. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN McELLIGOTT JR, Fullerton 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080694-0259 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 074871 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 6, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 2; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
